🤖 Synonym-Aware FAQ Bot – Basic Idea
🧠 Introduction

A Synonym-Aware FAQ Bot is a chatbot that answers user questions by understanding the meaning of the query, even if different words are used.

In real life, people ask the same question in many different ways. A normal FAQ system only works when the exact words match, but this bot improves that by recognizing synonyms and similar terms.
❗ Problem with Traditional FAQ Systems
Works only on exact keyword matching
Fails when wording changes

👉 Example:

Stored FAQ: “How to pay fees?”
User asks: “How can I pay tuition?”

❌ Traditional bot → No answer
✅ Synonym-aware bot → Correct answer

💡 What we Are Supposed to Build

You will build a system that:

1. Takes a user query

User types a question (e.g., “How do I make payment?”)

2. Understands similar words

It recognizes:

fees = tuition = payment = charges
3. Maps it to the correct FAQ

All similar queries are linked to one common intent

4. Returns the correct answer

Bot responds with the appropriate stored answer

🎯 Goal of the Project
Make FAQ systems smarter and more flexible
Improve user experience
Reduce manual support effort
